.TH "ring_buffer_record_disable_cpu" 9 "ring_buffer_record_disable_cpu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ring_buffer_record_disable_cpu \- stop all writes into the cpu_buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ring_buffer_record_disable_cpu
.BI "(struct trace_buffer *buffer "  ","
.BI "int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
The ring buffer to stop writes to.
.IP "cpu" 12
The CPU buffer to stop
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This prevents all writes to the buffer. Any attempt to write
to the buffer after this will fail and return NULL.

The caller should call \fBsynchronize_rcu\fP after this.
